The paper deals with a probabilistic formulation of sparse PCA and analyzes an Approximate Message Passing (AMP) algorithm to estimate the underlying signal. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of sparsity constraints, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Signal Processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with high-dimensional data, which is often studied in Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
